The day I wrote “Strangers Again” with @stephenhunley and @traftonharvey - I walked back to my place on music row, and immediately, excitedly played it for some friends I had over. (we were intending on going to the Hixtape @whiskeyjam takeover, before the roof caved in💀) I was encouraged by their response to the song to say the least. Sometimes you’re just done with a situation in your life with no intention of revisiting it, and that’s what this song is about.  I hope it helps you through whatever you’re going through. It’s so easy to say “we’ve all been there,” but I find songs tend to be better at reminding us we aren’t alone. It’s all yours now. Turn it up. Enjoy.  #newcountrymusic #countrymusicfriday #soulfulcountryrock #nashvilleartist
